#385

- Growing on brown-rot log on Northeast-facing slope in large mixed oak/hickory woodland draw. 
- Caps pale yellow with little hairy spines, some turning brownish especially on the top.
- Lamellae yellow, adnexed, with rough edges and unequal.
- Stipe similarly colored as cap and smooth.

Additional Info
- Smell: sweet
- Taste: faintly bitter
- Spore Print: white
